      "text": "I’m of a temperament that cannot cease seeing difference, while Robin belongs, I think, to the (larger? I think so) body of people who resonate with (hunger for?) alikeness. What ‘we’ need, I think, is a way of knowing and organising that embraces both these kinds of life; and many other potentials for fragmentation too, rendering them as effective, *living*, generative capacity: in making a *living* economy.\n\n"
